cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the optimization of the trajectory and deployment of multiple UAVs for collecting data from ground IoT devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a new approach for optimal mobility of UAVs, which involves the use of optimal transport theory, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with minimizing energy consumption, which is a topic covered in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of clustering algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes an approach for energy-efficient communications, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
